see [[default cards]], from wagn.org so needs some tweaking</em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>{{Set+*type|closed}}</p>\n<p>{{Settings+*type|closed}}</p>\n<p>{{list of rules|closed}}</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>{{Cardtype+*type|closed}}</p>\n<p>{{cardtype descriptions|closed}}</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>{{Role+*type|closed}}</p>\n<p>[[*account]], [[WagnBot]], [[Anonymous]]</p>\n<p>[[*to]], [[*from]], [[*thanks]], [[Invite Success]], [[Signup  Success]], [[Request Sent]]</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>[[Config]]</p>\n<p>{{Config+*inclusions|closed}}</p>\n<p>{{*sidebar+*inclusions|closed}}</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Related tab</h2>\n<blockquote>\n<p>[[*account+*right+*content]] - available on any card that has the account extension</p>\n<p>Available on every card, because they\'re in [[*related]]:</p>\n<p>{{Related subtabs - universal|closed}}</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Cards useful for Wagneering</h2>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>[[by name+*right+*content]]</p>\n<p>[[by update+*right+*content]]</p>\n<p>[[by create+*right+*content]]</p>\n<hr>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>Process</h1>\n<ol>\n<li>Everything about default Wagns that can be done within cards (except permissions, see below) happens here. Make changes that make sense to you, and watch what each other are doing on Recent. There\'s space for discussion at the bottom of this page if you like.</li>\n<li>To <strong>migrate</strong> cards you add or change here to existing Wagns, put  a note in the [[http://wagn.org/Next_Wagn_Release|next Wagn release\'s]]  discussion about which cards you want migrated.</li>\n<li>Cards that are <strong> deleted</strong> should also be noted as migrations if it would cause a problem to leave them in. Otherwise, add them to the list at  http://www.wagn.org/wagn/migrations+to_delete (we only migrate deletions once in a  while).</li>\n<li>Default [[http://wagn.org/wagn/initial_permissions|<strong>permissions</strong> are  specified on wagn.org]], because we want people to be able to choose among several different initial setups.</li>\n<li><strong>Document</strong> changes and additions at http://wagn.org/Default_cards and http://wagn.org/star_cards</li>\n<li>Things you remove from [[Config]] that may be relevant later can be added to http://www.wagn.org/wagn/en+not_ready</li>\n<li>Anything that involves code should be [[http://wagn.org/new/Ticket|ticketed]] on wagn.org</li>\n</ol>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>Todo</h1>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Content / Wagneering<br></h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Adapt or include [[default cards]] for the \"What comprises...\" section above.</li>\n<li>Test and tweak http://wagn.org/wagn/initial_permissions (ongoing)</li>\n<li>make *ignore a Search that returns Users, Account Requests, and things referred to by *ignore+tag. (Requires changing the dump a little, but could bring new users in with less overhead.)&nbsp; <em>eventually.&nbsp;&nbsp; not ready for this yet --efm</em></li>\n</ol>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Documentation<br></h2>\n<ul>\n<li>When documenting tickets that relate to [[http://wagn.org/wagn/Installation+tickets_for_item|installation]] or [[http://wagn.org/wagn/administration+tickets_for_item|administration]], make sure to update [[Config]]. (make search to show ones from current/recent releases?)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>Discussion</h1>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>'),(3929,6507,0,'Cards'),(3930,6507,1,'3'),(3932,6507,3,'1'),(3934,6497,0,'Wagn\'s Secret'),(3935,6497,1,'3'),(3936,6497,2,'<p>It\'s all in the cards.</p>'),(3937,6497,3,'1'),(3939,6507,2,'<p>\"Cards\" are Wagn\'s building blocks. Everything you do on Wagn involves creating, reading, updating, and deleting cards. Here\'s a simple one:</p>\r\n<blockquote>{{Wagn\'s Secret|open}}</blockquote>\r\n<p></p>'),(3945,6568,0,'Wagneer Menu'),(3946,6568,1,'3'),(3948,6568,3,'0'),(3949,6515,0,'Wagneer Menu+*self'),(3950,6515,1,'259'),(3951,6515,2,'{\"name\":\"_left\"}'),(3952,6515,3,'0'),(3953,6516,0,'Wagneer Menu+*self+*read'),(3954,6516,1,'47'),(3955,6516,2,'[[Administrator]]'),(3956,6516,3,'0'),(3958,6518,0,'*favicon+*self'),(3959,6518,1,'259'),(3960,6518,2,'{\"name\":\"_left\"}'),(3961,6518,3,'0'),(3962,6519,0,'*favicon+*self+*help'),(3963,6519,1,'3'),(3964,6519,2,'<p>A favicon (or shortcut icon) is a small image used by browsers to help identify your website. [[http://www.wagn.org/wagn/favicon|How to customize your favicon]]</p>'),(3965,6519,3,'0'),(3970,6528,0,'original'),(3971,6528,1,'3'),(3972,6528,2,''),(3973,6528,3,'0'),(3974,6555,0,'Home+original'),(3975,6555,1,'50'),(3977,6555,3,'0'),(4001,6555,2,'<h1>Create</h1>\r\n<em>Wagn. For the Organizing Artist</em>\r\n<aside>\r\n<h2>The Wagn Way</h2>\r\n<p>DRY: Don\'t Repeat Yourself. Most projects wind up with data copied all over the place: on the website, in a database, in email, etc. Wagn helps you organize data for use and reuse in many different contexts. When you update it once, you update it everywhere.</p>\r\n</aside>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<h2>Database</h2>\r\n<p>Complex structures without the complex interface. [[http://wagn.org/types|Types]], [[http://wagn.org/compound_names|compound names]], [[http://wagn.org/formatting|formatting]], and a native [[http://wagn.org/WQL|query language]] comprise a powerful bottom-up data-organizing toolset. <em>[[http://wagn.org/structure|Howto]]</em></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<h2>Website</h2>\r\n<p>[[http://wagn.org/layouts|Layouts]] and [[http://wagn.org/views|views]] help you present information flexibly and beautifully. <em>[[http://wagn.org/pages|Howto]]</em></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<h2>Workflow</h2>\r\n<p>Web submissions, project proposals, meeting records, customer info, research, sketches, reports... Wagn helps teams create, evolve, and connect all their information flows in fluid and adaptive ways. <em>[[http://wagn.org/wagneering|Howto]]</em></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h1>Collaborate</h1>\r\n<em>Wagn. Go Together</em>\r\n<aside>\r\n<h2>The Wagn Way</h2>\r\n<p>Any interface you don\'t use is noise. Wagn quiets edit interface for those who just want to read, quiets configuration interface quiet for those who just want to edit content, and quiets coding syntax for site managers.</p>\r\n</aside>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<h2>Accounts</h2>\r\n<p>Configure [[http://wagn.org/accounts|accounts]] and [[http://wagn.org/roles|roles]] to make your Wagn as open or closed as desired. <em>[[http://wagn.org/accounts|Howto]]</em></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<h2>Permissions</h2>\r\n<p>An elegant [[http://wagn.org/permissions|permissions]] system allows fine-grained control over who can create, read, update, and delete. <em>[[http://wagn.org/permissions|Howto]]</em></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<h2>History</h2>\r\n<p>Don\'t worry about breaking things. Every card has a revision [[http://wagn.org/history|history]], and even [[http://wagn.org/deleting|deleting]] cards doesn\'t permanently destroy them, it just puts them in the trash. So all changes can be reviewed and reversed. <em>[[http://wagn.org/history|Howto]]</em></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<h2>Evolution</h2>\r\n<p>Building great collaborative websites requires thoughtfully adapting technology to community needs. Wagn is designed to evolve with you. <em>[[http://wagn.org/wagneering|Howto]]</em></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h1>Explore</h1>\r\n<em>Wagn. How Pioneers Roll.</em>\r\n<aside>\r\n<h2>The Wagn Way</h2>\r\n<p>Context matters. Most web systems can only be managed in a separate \"admin area\", so fixing problems means shifting context entirely.  Wagn minimizes context shifts by letting you make changes in place wherever you see the need.</p>\r\n</aside>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<h2>Cards</h2>\r\n<p>[[http://wagn.org/cards|Cards]] are Wagn\'s building blocks. Everything  text, files, images, accounts, etc.  is in a card. <em>[[http://wagn.org/cards|Howto]]</em></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<h2>Types</h2>\r\n<p>Every card has a [[http://wagn.org/type|type]]. Many types, like [[http://wagn.org/users|users]], [[http://wagn.org/image|images]], and [[http://wagn.org/search|searches]], come with Wagn out of the box, and you can create new types as you go. <em>[[http://wagn.org/type|Howto]]</em></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<h2>Navbox</h2>\r\n<p>The [[http://wagn.org/navbox|navbox]] is a search bar, an auto-completer, and a shortcut for creating new cards. <em>[[http://wagn.org/navbox|Howto]]</em></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<h2>Menus</h2>\r\n<p>Card [[http://wagn.org/menus|menus]] let you navigate, edit, configure, and administer without shifting context. <em>[[http://wagn.org/menus|Howto]]</em></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<h2>Rules</h2>\r\n<p>The heart of configuring Wagn is creating [[http://wagn.org/rules|rules]].  Reached via the \"advanced\" menu item, rules control every aspect of a card\'s behavior and appearance, from [[http://wagn.org/permissions|permissions]] to [[http://wagn.org/formatting|formatting]] to [[http://wagn.org/help_text|help text]] and beyond. <em>[[http://wagn.org/rules|Howto]]</em></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n'),(4002,6556,2,':logo/05_standard.png'),(4011,6567,2,''),(4012,6568,2,'<p><strong>[[http://wagn.org/Features| features]]</strong>: [[http://wagn.org/cards|cards]], [[http://wagn.org/types|types]], [[http://wagn.org/inclusions|inclusions]], [[http://wagn.org/views|views]], [[http://wagn.org/rules|rules]], [[http://wagn.org/layouts|layouts]], [[http://wagn.org/formatting|formatting]], [[http://wagn.org/accounts|accounts]], [[http://wagn.org/permissions|permissions]]</p>\r\n<p><strong>[[http://wagn.org/Syntax Reference|syntax]]</strong>: [[http://wagn.org/link_syntax|links]], [[http://wagn.org/inclusion_syntax|inclusions]], [[http://wagn.org/WQL_syntax|queries]]</p>'),(4015,6574,2,'<p>HTML structure of card\'s page <em>[[http://wagn.org/layouts | more]]</em></p>'),(4016,6715,0,'CSS'),(4017,6715,1,'5'),(4018,6715,2,'<p>{{+description}}</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>[[/new/{{_self|linkname}}|add {{_self|name}} card]]</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>{{_self|name}} Cards</h1>\n<blockquote>\n<p>{{+*type+by name}}</p>\n</blockquote>'),(4019,6715,3,'0'),(4020,6716,0,'SCSS'),(402