ble.</p>'),(961,'2009-04-06 14:11:12',68,1,'<p>Your invitation is on its way to their emailbox now.</p>'),(963,'2009-04-06 14:11:12',108,1,'wagn/Request_Sent'),(973,'2009-04-06 14:11:12',80,1,'<h1>Welcome to your new Wagn!</h1>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>To get started, [[Config|set some important configuration options]].</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Reference</h2>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>[[http://wagn.org/wagn/configuration|Wagn Configuration]]</p>\n<p>[[http://wagn.org/wagn/Documentation|Wagn Documentation]]</p>'),(978,'2009-04-06 14:11:12',83,1,'<p>Contents will appear on right sidebar.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>'),(982,'2009-04-06 14:11:12',90,1,'<p>use \"off\" or \"on\" to force a table setting.</p>'),(1119,'2009-04-06 14:11:12',100,1,'<p>[[/account/invite|Invite a new user]]</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>{{Cards with accounts|titled}}</p>'),(1172,'2009-04-06 14:11:12',56,1,'<p><em>Any signed-in user with the [[/admin/tasks|global permission]] to \"create accounts\" can invite new users via email.</em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Default subject</h2>\n<blockquote>\n<p>{{+*subject|type:Phrase}}</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Default message</h2>\n<blockquote>\n<p>{{+*message|type:PlainText}}</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>After sending an invitation, you\'re taken here:</strong><span><strong></strong></span></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp; <span>HTTP:// <em>(YOUR WAGN\'S DOMAIN)</em></span><em> </em>/{{+*thanks}}</p>\n</blockquote>'),(1176,'2009-04-06 14:11:12',66,1,'<p>To let users sign up (with no approval process), [[*request|turn on account requests]], and give \"Anybody\" the [[/admin/tasks | global permission]] to create accounts.&nbsp; Newly registered users will be sent an email with a password and the following details:</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Email Subject.<br></h2>\n<blockquote>\n<p>{{*signup+*subject|type:Phrase}}</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Email Message</h2>\n<blockquote>\n<p>{{*signup+*message|closed;type:PlainText}}</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>As the email is sent, the<strong> person signing up will be sent here</strong>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><span>HTTP:// <em>(YOUR WAGN\'S DOMAIN)</em></span><em> </em>/{{+*thanks}}</p>\n</blockquote>'),(1177,'2009-04-06 14:11:12',63,1,'<p>Users can request accounts via a \"Sign Up\" link if you allow \"Anyone\" to [[/card/options/Account_Request|create account requests]].</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Unless [[*signup|approved automatically]], the <strong>request will be emailed to</strong>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>{{+*to|type:Phrase}}</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><strong>and the requester will be redirected here:</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <span>HTTP:// <em>(YOUR WAGN\'S DOMAIN)</em></span><em> </em>/{{+*thanks}}</p>'),(1225,'2009-04-06 14:11:12',110,1,''),(1242,'2009-04-06 14:11:12',113,1,''),(1253,'2009-04-06 14:11:12',115,1,''),(1269,'2009-04-06 14:11:12',112,1,'[[community]]\n[[plusses]]\n[[references]]'),(1270,'2009-04-06 14:11:12',117,1,''),(1275,'2009-04-06 14:11:12',120,1,'[[type]]'),(1276,'2009-04-06 14:11:12',121,1,''),(1283,'2009-04-06 14:11:12',123,1,'[[items]]'),(1284,'2009-04-06 14:11:12',124,1,''),(1309,'2009-04-06 14:11:12',73,1,'<h1>Basics</h1>\n<blockquote>\n<p><em>Site name (appears in browser\'s title bar):</em> {{*title|closed;type:Phrase}}</p>\n<p><em>Name of home card (if different from *title):</em> {{*home|closed;type:Phrase}}</p>\n<p>{{*logo|closed;type:image}}</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>Sidebar</h1>\n<blockquote>\n<p><em>[[http://wagn.org/wagn/sidebar|How to customize sidebar]].</em></p>\n<p>{{*sidebar|closed}}<em></em></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>Account basics</h1>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Invitations</h2>\n<p><em><br></em></p>\n<p><em>Settings for inviting new users, requesting accounts, and getting accounts approved.</em></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>{{*invite|closed}}</p>\n<p>{{*request|closed}}</p>\n<p>{{*signup|closed}}</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>Advanced</h1>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Appearance</h2>\n<blockquote>\n<p><em>See http://wagn.org/Skin for CSS examples.</em></p>\n<em></em>\n<p>{{*css|closed;type:HTML}}</p>\n<p>{{*favicon|closed;type:image}}</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Account information emails<br></h2>\n<blockquote>\n<p><em>\"From\" address for emails that deliver user account information. (I.e., when someone signs up, is invited/approved, or forgot their password).&nbsp; </em></p>\n<p>{{*account+*from|closed;type:Phrase}}</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Sign-up forms</h2>\n<blockquote>\n<p><em>[[http://wagn.org/wagn/custom_sign-up_information|How to create a custom sign-up form]]. <br></em></p>\n<p>{{Account Request+*tform|closed}}</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Edit toolbar</h2>\n<blockquote>\n<p><em>[[http://wagn.org/wagn/TinyMCE|How to customize the edit toolbar]].</em></p>\n<p>{{*tinyMCE|closed}}</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Google Analytics</h2>\n<blockquote>\n<p><em>[[http://wagn.org/wagn/Google_Analytics|How to set up Google Analytics for Wagns]]</em></p>\n<p>{{*google analytics key|type:Phrase}}</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><em></em></p>\n</blockquote>'),(1407,'2009-04-06 14:11:12',128,1,''),(1408,'2009-04-06 14:11:12',129,1,''),(1409,'2009-04-06 14:11:12',130,1,''),(1410,'2009-04-06 14:11:12',131,1,''),(1428,'2009-04-06 14:11:12',88,1,'<p>{{+description}}</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>{{_self|name}} Cards</h2>\n<blockquote>\n<p>{{+*instances}}</p>\n</blockquote>'),(1433,'2009-04-06 14:11:12',122,1,'<p>[[/new/{{_left|linkname}}|add a {{_left|name}} card]]</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>Form for {{_left|name}} cards<br></h1>\n<p>{{_left+*tform|closed}}</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>{{_left|name}} cards</h1>\n<p>{{_left+*instances}}</p>'),(1435,'2009-04-06 14:11:12',5,1,'<p>{{+description}}</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>{{_self|name}} Cards</h1>\n<blockquote>\n<p>{{+*instances}}</p>\n</blockquote>'),(1454,'2009-04-06 14:11:12',127,1,'<p>Test area:</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<hr>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>{{inclusion}}</p>\n<p>[[foo]]</p>\n<p>	esting if backslash monospaces regular text</p>\n<p>http://ourpla.net/</p>\n<p>irc.freenode.net</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<hr>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>{{*tform+*plus cards|closed;item:name}}</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<hr>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>[[foo+]]</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>[[foo+_self]]</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>[[foo+_whole]]</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>[[foo+_left]]</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>[[foo+_user]]</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>{{foo+}}</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>{{foo+_self}}</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>{{foo+_whole}}</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>{{foo+_right}}</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>{{foo+_user}}</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<hr>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>{{*logo|float:right}}{{DeleteMe}}</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>{{*logo|float:left}}{{DeleteMe}}</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>{{*logo|float:right}}{{DeleteMe|open}}</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>{{*logo|float:left}}{{DeleteMe|closed}}</p>'),(1455,'2009-04-06 14:11:12',135,1,'<p>{{DeleteMe|open}}</p>'),(1521,'2009-04-06 14:11:12',137,1,''),(1541,'2009-04-06 14:11:12',1,1,'<p>This is the account that makes any automated updates &mdash; cards created when someone signs up, link updates when renaming cards, etc.</p>'),(1550,'2009-04-06 14:11:12',138,1,''),(1551,'2009-04-06 14:11:12',119,1,'<h1>{{_left|name}}\'s roles<br></h1>\n<blockquote>\n<p>{{_left+*roles|item:link}}</p>\n</blockquote>\n<h1>Cards {{_left|name}} has edited</h1>\n<blockquote>\n<p>{{_left +*editing}}</p>\n</blockquote>'),(1563,'2009-04-06 14:11:12',125,1,'<p>Adding a +*options Search card to a Pointer limits the auto-completion to the cards returned by the Search. And if it\'s a simple search for a cardtype, then cards created through the pointer will automatically be set to that type.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>{{_left+*options}}</p>'),(1572,'2009-04-06 14:11:12',116,1,'<p>{{+tags|closed}}</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>{{_left+*editors|closed}}</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>{{+discussion|open}}</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</blockquote>'),(1573,'2009-04-06 14:11:12',91,1,'off'),(1631,'2009-04-06 14:11:12',114,1,'<h1>Links</h1>\n<p><em>Cards that <strong>{{_left|name}}</strong> links to:</em></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>{{_left+links}}</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><em>Cards that link to <strong>{{_left|name}}</strong>:</em></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>{{_left+linkers}}</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>Inclusions</h1>\n<p><em>Cards that <strong>{{_left|name}}</strong> includes:</em></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>{{_left+inclusions}}</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><em>Cards that include <strong>{{_left|name}}</strong>:</em></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>{{_left+includers}}</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>'),(1690,'2009-04-06 14:11:12',144,1,'[[users]]'),(1694,'2009-04-06 14:11:12',145,1,'<h1>Accounts with the {{_left|name}} role<br></h1>\n<blockquote>\n<p>{{_left+*users}}</p>\n</blockquote>'),(1696,'2009-04-06 14:11:12',146,1,''),(1697,'2009-04-06 14:11:12',147,1,'<p>Administrators automatically have all of the [[/admin/tasks|global permissions]].</p>'),(1701,'2009-04-06 14:11:12',7,1,'<p>Each role\'s capabilities are defined in [[/admin/tasks|Global permissions]] (except for the Administrator role, which has all permissions).</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>[[/new/Role|Add a new role]]</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>Roles</h1>\n<p>{{+*instances}}</p>'),(1703,'2009-04-06 14:11:12',105,1,'<p>{{+description}}</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>Accounts with the {{_self|name}} role<br></h1>\n<blockquote>\n<p>{{+*users}}</p>\n</blockquote>'),(1710,'2009-04-06 14:11:12',118,1,'[[account]]'),(1711,'2009-04-06 14:11:12',148,1,''),(1722,'2009-04-06 14:11:12',111,1,'<p><em>Plus cards</em> have a plus (+) in their name <em>(e.g., \"Menu+description\")</em>. They are formed by plussing two cards together to make a third.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Plus Cards</h2>\n<p><em>Cards of which <strong>{{_left|name}}</strong> is part</em></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>{{_left+*plus cards}}</p>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><br></h2>\n<h2>Parts<br></h2>\n<p><em>Cards that form plus cards with <strong>{{_left|name}}</strong></em></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>{{_left+*plus parts}}</p>\n</blockquote>'),(1729,'2009-04-06 14:11:12',55,1,''),(1730,'2009-04-06 17:32:45',149,1,''),(1731,'2009-04-06 17:33:18',150,149,''),(1737,'2009-04-06 17:54:16',68,149,'<p>Your invitation is on its way.</p>'),(1738,'2009-04-06 17:54:30',68,149,'<p>Thanks!&nbsp; Your invitation is on its way.</p>'),(1740,'2009-04-07 12:00:58',151,149,'<p>[[*account|Accounts]]</p>\n<p>[[Roles]]</p>\n<p>[[/admin/tasks|Global permissions]]</p>'),(1741,'2009-04-07 13:18:29',152,149,'<p><strong><em><span>Cards and [[images]] in this Wagn are copied to new Wagns</span></em>. Exceptions should be added here:</strong></p>\n<p>{{*ignore|closed}}</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>This one updates automatically:</strong></p>\n<p>{{cards to copy to new Wagns|closed}}</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>What comprises those cards</h1>\n<p>(There may be some duplicates, and you can ignore exceptions such as the Ethan, Lewis &amp; John cards.)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Account-related</h2>\n<blockquote>\n<p>[[*account]]</p>\n<p>{{Role+*instances|closed}}</p>\n<p>{{User+*instances|closed}}</p>\n<p>[[*to]], [[*from]], [[*thanks]], [[Invite Success]], [[Signup Success]], [[Request Sent]]<br> {{*thanks+*plus cards|closed}}</p>\n</blockquote>\n<h2>Cardtypes and forms</h2>\n<blockquote>\n<p>{{Cardtype+*instances|closed}}</p>\n<p>[[*tform]], [[*rform]]</p>\n<p>{{*tform+*plus cards|closed}}</p>\n<p>{{*rform+*plus cards|closed}}</p>\n<p>(if any are deleted, you\'ll probably want to delete the left part as well)</p>\n</blockquote>\n<h2>Config and help text</h2>\n<blockquote>\n<p>[[Config]]</p>\n<p>{{Config+inclusions|closed}}</p>\n<p>{{*sidebar+inclusions|closed}}</p>\n<p>[[*edit]]</p>\n<p>{{*edit+*plus cards|closed}}</p>\n</blockquote>\n<h2>Related tab</h2>\n<p>(Note that in these +*rform cards, _left returns the name of the card on which one is viewing the Related tab.)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Available on every card, because they\'re in [[*context]]:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>{{universal Related tabs}}</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Available on [[Pointers]] (item), [[Cardtypes]] (type), and cards with an account extension (typically, [[User]] cards &mdash; Role). Because they\'re in [[*context+*plus cards]]:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>{{custom Related tabs}}</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<hr>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>Process</h1>\n<ol>\n<li>Everything that can be done within cards is happening here. Just do things, and watch what each other are doing on Recent, and there\'s space for discussion at the bottom of this page.</li>\n<li>Everything that involves code is on [[http://wagn.org/wagn/implement_initial_setup_for_new_Wagn|the relevant ticket on wagn.org]] (everything there that was doable in cards has been done, or copied here).</li>\n<li>Things that probably need work before the 1.0 launch are <strong>bold</strong>.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>A lot of work happens on <strong>[[Config]]</strong>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>[[http://wagn.org/wagn/configuration|configuration]]</strong> needs work to reflect changes.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>delete [[Setting]], [[Currency]], [[Percentage]], [[RichText]]</strong> - waiting on http://wagn.org/wagn/Can_t_remove_or_change_Cardtype_of_Cardtype_cards</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>[[Cardtype+*tform]] (when pretty stable, copy/adapt to other [[cardtypes]])</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>[[Signup Success]], [[Invite Success]], [[Request Sent]]</strong> - fuller explanation?</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Documentation:</p>\n<p>more links on [[Config]]</p>\n<p>more +*edit on cardtypes?</p>\n<p>??</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>[[*logo]] - make sure re licensing</p>\n<p>[[Home]] - link to /admin/setup and more welcome/explanatory text, ??</p>\n<p>[[*css]] - useful comments; template content?</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Viewable only by Administrator:</p>\n<p>[[Account Request+*tform]]</p>\n<p>[[Administrator links]]</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Editable only by Administrator:</p>\n<p>[[*context]]</p>\n<p>[[*to]]</p>\n<p>[[*from]]</p>\n<p>?</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Ongoing work<br></h2>\n<p>Update http://wagn.org/wagn/star_cards</p>\n<p>When documenting tickets that relate to [[http://wagn.org/wagn/Installation+tickets_for_item|installation]] or [[http://wagn.org/wagn/administration+tickets_for_item|administration]], make sure to update [[Config]].</p>\n<p>Take a look at http://wagn.org/wagn/cards_to_include_by_default once in a while</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>Discussion<br></h1>\n<hr>\n<p>[[*instances+*rform]] is in default, last-edited order. Sort alpha?</p>\n<p><em>&nbsp;&nbsp;--[[John Abbe]].....Mon Mar 02 08:10:02 -0800 2009</em></p>\n<hr>\n<p>I did a bunch of work on this today.  My focal points were:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>getting rid of text. I think we want as little text as possible in this thing, because every line of text is something that could later prove wrong or awkward, and it will be hard to update. I\'d much rather link off to wagn.org (though I would hope that most users could avoid having to use much documentation).</li>\n<li>trimming blank cards where possible. John and I may want to discuss. Before we wanted a lot of those blank cards there to have the right default type, but I\'m now kind of inclined to take them off and let the default setting handle it.</li>\n<li>I moved a lot of the (much trimmed) signup information into *signup, *request, and *invite. The paragraphs there seemed like overkill to me. I\'d like to do even less.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br>I took off the [[All cards]] card (for now) because the wql is rough, the name is confusing, and the use case is very fuzzy to me.<br><br>I\'d like to propose removing Script and Ruby cards from the default setup.<br><br>I\'m also seriously considering reopening the \"redirect\" card conversation, which might be really useful for handling the *thanks and *home cards more coherently (they\'re essentially redirects).<br><br>I left out the success cards for now thinking a good solution for how to include them might come out of the redirect conversation. If not they\'ll need to be more accessible from Config.<br><br>I can also see adding a link to documentation about open-edit wagns to the bottom of the Account Basics section on the Config card, but I wouldn\'t want those instructions inline, since that may be changing in a hurry.</p>\n<p><em>&nbsp;&nbsp;--[[Ethan McCutchen]].....Fri Mar 13 14:18:52 -0700 2009</em></p>\n<hr>\n<p>I delete *google analytics keys and almost all of the email related cards.</p>\n<p><em>&nbsp;&nbsp;--[[Ethan McCutchen]].....Fri Mar 13 18:49:13 -0700 2009</em></p>\n<hr>\n<p>I\'d like to see us start working on the new Related Tab here this week.</p>\n<p><em>&nbsp;&nbsp;--[[Ethan McCutchen]].....Fri Mar 13 18:59:12 -0700 2009</em></p>'),(1742,'2009-04-07 13:19:28',153,149,'{\"not\": {\"referred_to_by\": \"cards to not copy to new Wagns\"},\n \"sort\": \"alpha\",\n \"limit\": 200\n}'),(1743,'2009-04-07 13:20:39',154,149,'[[Ethan McCutchen]]'),(1744,'2009-04-07 13:21:44',154,149,'[[Ethan McCutchen]]\n[[John Abbe]]\n[[cards to copy to new Wagns]]'),(1745,'2009-04-07 13:22:12',154,149,'[[Ethan McCutchen]]\n[[John Abbe]]\n[[cards to copy to new Wagns]]\n[[*ignore]]'),(1746,'2009-04-07 13:22:42',153,149,'{\"not\": {\"referred_to_by\": \"*ignore\"},\n \"sort\": \"alpha\",\n \"limit\": 200\n}'),(1747,'2009-04-07 13:29:24',155,149,''),(1748,'2009-04-08 08:59:14',156,150,''),(1754,'2009-04-08 10:03:06',152,150,'<p><em><span>Cards and [[images]] in this Wagn are copied to new Wagns</span></em>. Exceptions should be added here:</p>\n<p>{{*ignore|closed}}</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>This one updates automatically:</p>\n<p>{{cards to copy to new Wagns|closed}}</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>[[http://wagn.org/wagn/initial_permissions|Permissions are designed on wagn.org]] because there are multiple initial setups.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>What comprises those cards</h1>\n<p>(There may be some duplicates, and you can ignore exceptions such as the Ethan, Lewis &amp; John cards.)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Account-related</h2>\n<blockquote>\n<p>[[*account]]</p>\n<p>{{Role+*instances|closed}}</p>\n<p>{{User+*instances|closed}}</p>\n<p>[[*to]], [[*from]], [[*thanks]], [[Invite Success]], [[Signup Success]], [[Request Sent]]<br> {{*thanks+*plus cards|closed}}</p>\n</blockquote>\n<h2>Cardtypes and forms</h2>\n<blockquote>\n<p>{{Cardtype+*instances|closed}}</p>\n<p>[[*tform]], [[*rform]]</p>\n<p>{{*tform+*plus cards|closed}}</p>\n<p>{{*rform+*plus cards|closed}}</p>\n<p>(if any are deleted, you\'ll probably want to delete the left part as well)</p>\n</blockquote>\n<h2>Config and help text</h2>\n<blockquote>\n<p>[[Config]]</p>\n<p>{{Config+inclusions|closed}}</p>\n<p>{{*sidebar+inclusions|closed}}</p>\n<p>[[*edit]]</p>\n<p>{{*edit+*plus cards|closed}}</p>\n</blockquote>\n<h2>Related tab</h2>\n<p>(Note that in these +*rform cards, _left returns the name of the card on which one is viewing the Related tab.)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Available on every card, because they\'re in [[*context]]:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>{{universal Related tabs}}</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Available on [[Pointers]] (item), [[Cardtypes]] (type), and cards with an account extension (typically, [[User]] cards &mdash; Role). Because they\'re in [[*context+*plus cards]]:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>{{custom Related tabs}}</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<hr>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>Process</h1>\n<ol>\n<li>Everything that can be done within cards is happening here. Just do things, and watch what each other are doing on Recent, and there\'s space for discussion at the bottom of this page.</li>\n<li>Everything that involves code is on [[http://wagn.org/wagn/implement_initial_setup_for_new_Wagn|the relevant ticket on wagn.org]] (everything there that was doable in cards has been done, or copied here).</li>\n<li>Things that probably need work before the 1.0 launch are <strong>bold</strong>.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>&n