>\n<p>[[Home]] - link to /admin/setup and more welcome/explanatory text, ??</p>\n<p>[[*css]] - useful comments; template content?</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Ongoing work<br></h2>\n<p>Update http://wagn.org/wagn/star_cards</p>\n<p>When documenting tickets that relate to [[http://wagn.org/wagn/Installation+tickets_for_item|installation]] or [[http://wagn.org/wagn/administration+tickets_for_item|administration]], make sure to update [[Config]].</p>\n<p>Take a look at http://wagn.org/wagn/cards_to_include_by_default once in a while</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>Discussion<br></h1>\n<hr>\n<p>[[*instances+*rform]] is in default, last-edited order. Sort alpha?</p>\n<p><em>&nbsp;&nbsp;--[[John Abbe]].....Mon Mar 02 08:10:02 -0800 2009</em></p>\n<hr>\n<p>I did a bunch of work on this today.  My focal points were:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>getting rid of text. I think we want as little text as possible in this thing, because every line of text is something that could later prove wrong or awkward, and it will be hard to update. I\'d much rather link off to wagn.org (though I would hope that most users could avoid having to use much documentation).</li>\n<li>trimming blank cards where possible. John and I may want to discuss. Before we wanted a lot of those blank cards there to have the right default type, but I\'m now kind of inclined to take them off and let the default setting handle it.</li>\n<li>I moved a lot of the (much trimmed) signup information into *signup, *request, and *invite. The paragraphs there seemed like overkill to me. I\'d like to do even less.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br>I took off the [[All cards]] card (for now) because the wql is rough, the name is confusing, and the use case is very fuzzy to me.<br><br>I\'d like to propose removing Script and Ruby cards from the default setup.<br><br>I\'m also seriously considering reopening the \"redirect\" card conversation, which might be really useful for handling the *thanks and *home cards more coherently (they\'re essentially redirects).<b