e with accounts generally have a User card. To learn more, read the [[http://wagn.org/wagn/User|documentation about User cards]].</p>'),(2095,'2009-04-24 12:00:07',182,149,'<p>Search cards use [[http://wagn.org/wagn/WQL| WQL, the Wagn Query Language]].&nbsp; See [[http://wagn.org/wagn/WQL |syntax documentation]].</p>'),(2096,'2009-04-24 12:46:47',12,149,'<p>{{+description}}</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>{{_self|name}} Cards</h2>\n<blockquote>\n<p>{{+*type cards+by update}}</p>\n</blockquote>'),(2097,'2009-04-24 14:40:02',173,149,'{\"right_plus\":[\"tags\", {\"refer_to\":\"_self\"}]}'),(2173,'2009-04-24 22:25:22',152,150,'<p><em><span>Cards and [[images]] in this Wagn are copied to new Wagns</span></em>. Exceptions should be added here:</p>\n<p>{{*ignore|closed}}</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>This one updates automatically:</p>\n<p>{{cards to copy to new Wagns|closed}}</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>What comprises those cards</h1>\n<p>(There may be some duplicates, and you can ignore exceptions such as the Ethan, Lewis &amp; John cards.)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Account-related</h2>\n<blockquote>\n<p>[[*account]]</p>\n<p>{{Role+*type cards|closed}}</p>\n<p>{{User+*type cards|closed}}</p>\n<p>[[*to]], [[*from]], [[*thanks]], [[Invite Success]], [[Signup Success]], [[Request Sent]]<br> {{*thanks+*plus cards|closed}}</p>\n</blockquote>\n<h2>Cardtypes and forms</h2>\n<blockquote>\n<p>{{Cardtype+*type cards|closed}}</p>\n<p>[[*tform]], [[*rform]]</p>\n<p>{{*tform+*plus cards|closed}}</p>\n<p>{{*rform+*plus cards|closed}}</p>\n<p>(if any are deleted, you\'ll probably want to delete the left part as well)</p>\n</blockquote>\n<h2>Config and help text</h2>\n<blockquote>\n<p>[[Config]]</p>\n<p>{{Config+*inclusions|closed}}</p>\n<p>{{*sidebar+*inclusions|closed}}</p>\n<p>[[*edit]]</p>\n<p>{{*edit+*plus cards|closed}}</p>\n</blockquote>\n<h2>Related tab</h2>\n<p>(Note that in these +*rform cards, _left returns the name of the card on which one is viewing the Related tab.)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Available on every card, because they\'re in [[*related]]:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>{{universal Related tabs}}</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Available on [[Cardtypes]] (type), and cards with an account extension (account), because they\'re [[*related+*plus cards|plussed to *related]]:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>{{custom Related tabs}}</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>The config subtab has complexities that require code to implement, but we design it here:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>{{config subtab|closed}}</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<hr>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>Process</h1>\n<ol>\n<li>Everything about default Wagns that can be done within cards happens here. Make changes that make sense to you, and watch what each other are doing on Recent. There\'s space for discussion at the bottom of this page if you like.</li>\n<li>[[http://wagn.org/wagn/initial_permissions|Permissions are designed on wagn.org]] because there are multiple initial setups &mdash; default (public view, signin for edit), open-edit, ???.</li>\n<li>Everything that involves code is worked out ?where?. Original development was described on [[http://wagn.org/wagn/implement_initial_setup_for_new_Wagn|implement initial setup for new Wagns]].</li>\n</ol>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>Todo</h1>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Content / Wagneering<br></h2>\n<ol>\n<li>[[Cardtype+*tform]] (when pretty stable, copy/adapt to other [[cardtypes]])</li>\n<li>\n<p>[[*logo]] - make sure re licensing</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Test and tweak http://wagn.org/wagn/initial_permissions&nbsp;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Minimalist Help card in sidebar? (open/close icon, link to full docs, request questions and permision comments on)&nbsp;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>more +*edit on cardtypes?</p>\n</li>\n<li>We built in [[by updated]]. Add [[by created]], [[by name]], [[by content]], ??</li>\n</ol><ol> </ol>\n<h2>Coding</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>test/design final on config tab</li>\n<li>change to *related</li>\n<li>get rid of *\'s on tab</li>\n<li>add pieces to config (?)</li>\n</ol>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>D